Bharti Airtel’s Kenyan Unit to Start 3G Services in September, Daily Says

-- B y   E r i c   O m b o k
-- 
2011-07-21T04:06:22Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-21/bharti-airtel-s-kenyan-unit-to-start-3g-services-in-september-daily-says.html
Bharti Airtel Ltd. (BHARTI) ’s Kenyan unit
will start offering third-generation telecommunication services
in September, Business Daily reported, citing Chief Executive
Officer Rene Meza.  Airtel  Kenya  will complete technical and billing tests in
Nairobi and Mombasa over the next two months, the Nairobi-based
newspaper said.  In January, the company said it would begin the offering
so-called 3G services by the end of March.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Eric Ombok in Nairobi at 
 eombok@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
 Paul Richardson  at 
 pmrichardson@bloomberg.net  